Singapore Stocks: Cosco, Singapore Exchange, STX OSV Holdings

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 
2011-03-28T09:35:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/8telecom-cosco-corp-noble-reyoung-singapore-stocks-preview.html
Singapore ’s Straits Times Index
dropped 0.40 percent to 3,057.38 at the close. Two stocks
declined for each that rose in the benchmark index of 30
companies.  Shares on the measure trade at an average 14.1 times
 estimated earnings , compared with about 15.6 times at the end of
2010, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  The following shares were among the most active in the
market. Stock symbols are in parentheses after the company name.  Cosco Corp. Singapore Ltd. (COS SP), a China-based
shipbuilder, climbed 2.5 percent to S$2.06. The company said it
signed an agreement to build two drilling platforms, valued at
$525 million each, for Sevan Drilling Group.  Koon Holdings Ltd. (KNH)  , a construction company,
advanced 3.6 percent to 29 Singapore cents. The company said it
won a contract, valued at S$15.3 million ($12 million), to build
roads at an industrial park project in Singapore.  Singapore Exchange  Ltd. (SGX SP), which is pursuing a bid
for  Australia ’s ASX Ltd., lost 0.9 percent to S$7.78. DMG &
Partners Securities Pte lowered its share-price forecast to
S$8.90 from S$9.45, while maintaining its “buy”
recommendation.  STX OSV Holdings Ltd. (SOH)  , the world’s biggest maker
of oil-rig support vessels by sales, gained 1.7 percent to
S$1.17. The company said it won an order for the design and
construction of a platform supply vessel for NorSea Group AS.
Financial details were not disclosed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
